s MT'; font-size:12pt">'s on the green lanes perceived, following detailed research, to be most in danger the same is not true of neighbouring authorities.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">I had long been aware of comments about the route over Deadman's Hill which being in Nidderdale falls outside the NP boundary. An improvement to the summer Sunday bus service enabled me to visit it about 2 years ago. I was horrified at the enormous depth of the ruts going up the hillside and forming a wide ribbon of erosion. Pressures were being put on North Yorkshire CC to place a permanent </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">TRO</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> on the route. However, despite considerable public pressure, they decided to place only a temporary </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">TRO</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> which runs out shortly. The current lack of any right of appeal frustrates users of the route. The inclusion of the modification suggested above would be a big help.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">5 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>